    <h2>Skip these until later</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Multiple docks:</strong> buy one for a real room or display, not every possible setup.</li>
      <li><strong>Ultra-cheap high-capacity cards:</strong> fake-capacity storage is a common way to lose time and data.</li>
      <li><strong>Heavy battery packs for couch play:</strong> if you play near outlets, a good charger is simpler.</li>
      <li><strong>Accessory bundles with unknown brands:</strong> bundles can be fine, but one bad cable or card can create harder-to-debug charging and storage problems.</li>
    </ul>

